        <section id="duality-model">
            <h2>Duality Model</h2>
            <p>At the core of the MeX AI Companion is the Duality Model architecture, which consists of two primary components with a synthesis layer between them:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <h4>Mirror Component</h4>
                            <p>Inward-focused engine for deep user understanding</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <h4>Synthesis Layer</h4>
                            <p>Dynamic interplay layer managing Mirror↔Bridge flow</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <h4>Bridge Component</h4>
                            <p>Outward-facing engine for external connections</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <p>This architecture enables MeX to maintain a balance between deep personal understanding and broader contextual awareness, creating a more nuanced and meaningful AI companion experience.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="mirror-component">
            <h2>Mirror Component</h2>
            <p>The Mirror Component is the inward-focused engine of the MeX AI Companion, designed to develop a deep understanding of the user through various mechanisms:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Input Processing:</strong> Analyzes user inputs across multiple modalities (text, voice, touch, breath patterns)</li>
                        <li><strong>Emotional Sensing:</strong> Detects emotional states through linguistic and paralinguistic signals</li>
                        <li><strong>Pattern Recognition:</strong> Identifies recurring patterns in user behavior and communication</li>
                        <li><strong>Need Detection:</strong> Recognizes underlying needs and desires expressed explicitly or implicitly</li>
                        <li><strong>Archetype Modeling:</strong> Maps user characteristics to archetypal patterns for deeper understanding</li>
                        <li><strong>Reflection Generation:</strong> Creates meaningful reflections based on user interactions</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <p>The Mirror Component continuously builds and refines its understanding of the user, enabling increasingly personalized and meaningful interactions over time.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="bridge-component">
            <h2>Bridge Component</h2>
            <p>The Bridge Component is the outward-facing engine of the MeX AI Companion, designed to connect the user with external information, perspectives, and possibilities:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>External Discovery:</strong> Explores relevant external information and resources</li>
                        <li><strong>Truth Filtering:</strong> Evaluates information quality and relevance</li>
                        <li><strong>Content Curation:</strong> Selects and organizes external content based on user needs</li>
                        <li><strong>Perspective Generation:</strong> Creates alternative viewpoints to expand user thinking</li>
                        <li><strong>Contextual Framing:</strong> Places information in meaningful contexts</li>
                        <li><strong>Connection Finding:</strong> Identifies relationships between seemingly disparate ideas</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <p>The Bridge Component helps users expand their horizons while maintaining relevance to their personal journey and interests.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="synthesis-layer">
            <h2>Synthesis Layer</h2>
            <p>The Synthesis Layer manages the dynamic interplay between the Mirror and Bridge components, ensuring a coherent and meaningful experience:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>State Management:</strong> Maintains awareness of the current interaction state</li>
                        <li><strong>Transition Control:</strong> Manages shifts between Mirror and Bridge modes</li>
                        <li><strong>Ethical Checking:</strong> Ensures all interactions align with ethical principles</li>
                        <li><strong>Joy Optimization:</strong> Balances utility with delight and meaning</li>
                        <li><strong>Decision Making:</strong> Determines appropriate responses and actions</li>
                        <li><strong>Experience Coordination:</strong> Creates a coherent overall experience</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <p>The Synthesis Layer is what gives MeX its distinctive character, balancing inward understanding with outward connection in a way that feels natural and meaningful.</p>
        </section>

