        </section>

        <section id="data-architecture">
            <h2>Data Architecture</h2>
            <p>The MeX AI Companion employs a sophisticated data architecture designed to balance personalization with privacy:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h4>Core Principles</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Local-First Processing:</strong> Prioritizes on-device processing whenever possible</li>
                        <li><strong>Differential Privacy:</strong> Applies noise to data when aggregation is necessary</li>
                        <li><strong>Federated Learning:</strong> Improves models without centralizing raw user data</li>
                        <li><strong>User Sovereignty:</strong> Gives users control over their data through clear permissions</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4 class="mt-4">Data Types</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>User Profile Data:</strong> Core information about user preferences and patterns</li>
                        <li><strong>Interaction Data:</strong> Records of conversations and engagements</li>
                        <li><strong>Sensor Data:</strong> Information from device sensors (touch, motion, etc.)</li>
                        <li><strong>Derived Insights:</strong> Patterns and conclusions drawn from raw data</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <p>This architecture ensures that MeX can provide deeply personalized experiences while respecting user privacy and maintaining data security.</p>
        </section>

